---
/**
 * mvcc-internals-deep-dive · Figure 2 — the snapshot (xmin/xmax/xip[]) + the
 * two visibility gates.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/transactions-isolation/mvcc-internals-deep-dive.html (Level 2 figure).
 * Component, not inline MDX, for the kebab-case SVG attr reason (see Fig1).
 * References NO arrowhead markers, so it needs no local <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 180"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A snapshot is xmin oldest running, xmax first unassigned, and xip the in-progress list; visibility needs xmin past-and-committed and xmax not-past"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="14" y="14" width="178" height="56" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="103"
                y="34"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">snapshot.xmin</text
            >
            <text x="103" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >oldest xid still running</text
            >
            <rect x="211" y="14" width="178" height="56" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="34"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">snapshot.xmax</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >first id not yet assigned</text
            >
            <rect x="408" y="14" width="178" height="56" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="497"
                y="34"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">xip[ ]</text
            >
            <text x="497" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >ids in progress right now</text
            >
            <!-- two gates -->
            <rect x="40" y="100" width="250" height="64" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="165"
                y="122"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">GATE 1 — xmin is past</text
            >
            <text x="165" y="139" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >xmin committed, &lt; snapshot.xmax,</text
            >
            <text x="165" y="153" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >not in xip[ ] (creator visible)</text
            >
            <rect x="310" y="100" width="250" height="64" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="435"
                y="122"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">GATE 2 — xmax is NOT past</text
            >
            <text x="435" y="139" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >xmax=0/aborted, ≥ snapshot.xmax,</text
            >
            <text x="435" y="153" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >or in xip[ ] (deleter not done)</text
            >
            <text
                x="300"
                y="92"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">VISIBLE ⇔ both gates pass</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Plain English: <strong
            >you see a version created by a txn that committed before your snapshot, and not yet
            deleted by a txn that committed before your snapshot.</strong
        > That is the whole of snapshot isolation.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
